316
00:18:05,495 --> 00:18:09,675
Be not afraid. Fear not the name of the Reaper.

317
00:18:16,452 --> 00:18:18,275
And I got a super great deal!

318
00:18:18,300 --> 00:18:19,300
Yeah you did!

319
00:18:22,026 --> 00:18:23,391
It's so fizzy!

320
00:18:23,783 --> 00:18:27,586
Excellent! Quite a few more of you
showed up than I'd been led to expect.

321
00:18:28,032 --> 00:18:29,842
In the event that no one bothered to come,

322
00:18:29,953 --> 00:18:31,502
I was contemplating seppuku.

323
00:18:31,561 --> 00:18:34,164
Oh. Guess we really shouldn't have showed up, huh?

324
00:18:36,668 --> 00:18:39,924
Chiba? Hayami? Why are you guys so depressed?

325
00:18:40,579 --> 00:18:42,745
We both got banned from the shooting gallery.

326
00:18:42,821 --> 00:18:45,342
It was so easy we sorta got carried away.

327
00:18:46,419 --> 00:18:47,877
We needed the practice.

328
00:18:48,426 --> 00:18:52,104
So far I've only scored as high
as fifth place on any of your games.

329
00:18:52,577 --> 00:18:55,830
Seeing as that drives down the probability
of winning fourth place or above to,

330
00:18:55,913 --> 00:18:57,996
hold on, let me give you a concrete figure.

331
00:18:58,111 --> 00:19:00,597
Hey, how 'bout that? 0.05.

332
00:19:00,785 --> 00:19:03,155
I was wondering if the prizes are worth what I've spent.

333
00:19:03,246 --> 00:19:06,080
I mean, if you don't trust my
math, we could always ask a cop.

334
00:19:06,163 --> 00:19:07,572
All right, I get it.

335
00:19:07,843 --> 00:19:09,801
You can have your money back. Just keep quiet.

336
00:19:09,830 --> 00:19:11,227
Oh, I don't think so.

337
00:19:11,448 --> 00:19:13,612
I didn't blow my cash to get a refund.

338
00:19:14,038 --> 00:19:15,526
I want that game console.

339
00:19:16,038 --> 00:19:18,011
Karma sure is persistent.

340
00:19:18,330 --> 00:19:21,436
He knew that guy was a cheap
before he even started playing.

341
00:19:22,913 --> 00:19:23,827
Ooh.

342
00:19:24,011 --> 00:19:27,586
Seriously, man, is there anything you can't
do, or are you just that freakin' awesome?

343
00:19:27,735 --> 00:19:28,878
It's all in the wrist.

344
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:31,434
You've gotta flick like you
would if you were holding knife.

345
00:19:31,788 --> 00:19:32,694
That oughta do it.

346
00:19:33,663 --> 00:19:34,887
Okay, good haul.

347
00:19:35,205 --> 00:19:37,723
See, this is how you make a feast when you're dirt poor.

348
00:19:37,905 --> 00:19:38,716
I hear ya'.

349
00:19:38,804 --> 00:19:40,680
Should I pan fry them or go sashimi?

350
00:19:40,760 --> 00:19:42,450
Wait. That's his dinner?

351
00:19:43,222 --> 00:19:45,159
Wow. Everybody's raking it in.

